caption: Ready food with wonderful service.
Delicious food! I still remember their amazing fried chicken
Job security
Delicious as always. So accommodating to the different needs of my group.
Always great service and selection
Great bourbon selection and prices too!
Horrible customer service. Ridiculous food pairings for Valentine's day special.  They actually served us Macaroons and called it a dessert course!
Outstanding food in a unique atmosphere. Wonderful vibe and attentive staff.
Quiet dinner spot with excellent food and service.
Great atmosphere, really good food, and just a great evening.

I may be missing something when it comes to this place... But if you are looking for a traditional steakhouse or Italian restaurant (like we thought we were getting) you will be thoroughly disappointed with the food....  The menu seems very haphazard with no direction whatsoever. The short rib dish was totally underserved in the rib department (2.5” of “rib” on a large piece of cornbread served on a bowl of corn). All three short rib dishes in our party were left totally unfinished and were sent back to the kitchen. The amount short rib was very meager, our family members felt the portions were unfair for a $40 menu item.  The gnocchi was absolutely awful... I come from an Italian family I cannot believe such a simple Italian favourite was messed up so badly. The dish seemed to be more like triangular shaped tofu than an Italian gnocchi. The sauce and liquid it was served with was inedible...  Anyways, this seems like a pretty harsh review and I guess it is. This was just a dinner meeting amongst a group of friends all from far distances that happens only once a year for our group, so it was pretty unfortunate.  To be fair the manager took all of the items off the bill and offered us alternatives which we refused (our problem, I know). We were also given free coffees as a thank you.  The reason why I wrote this is because us I want other perspective patrons to know this is more of a vegan/granola/health food style restaurant and not an Italian restaurant or steakhouse at all (which is what we thought we were getting).  The reviews looked great but I knew something was off as the place was pretty empty on a Saturday night at 7PM when we arrived.  Maybe it was an off night...
Slowest service. Waited more than 40 minutes for a burger and small salad.
Fabulous food.
Great atmosphere ( if a but noisy when full), attentive service, innovative cuisine. The Roman style gnocchi ( deconstructed, sans pasts), were a surprise and a tasty delight.
Great presentation of food. Amazing services. Great atmosphere. Food was fresh and well organised. Interior was beautiful.

We came here to do a mini bourbon tasting and it was one of the better bars that we checked out on the urban bourbon trail.  The staff was incredibly knowledgeable and their recommendation (a special Woodford reserve bottling) was one of the favorite bourbons of the trip.  They also had lots of insight into the right places to visit and the right other ones to try.  And a decent local beer selection.  Overall a great set of sippers and really enjoyed the place.

Cannot say enough good things about our experience here. Everyone was friendly. Old fashioned was made PERFECTLY - Manhattan was also very good. The ambiance is elegant but welcoming. Definitely give Marketplace a try on your Urban Bourbon Trail adventure. I wish I could remember our waiter/bartenders name, but he was also very kind and knowledgeable about bourbons. Experiences like this one are reasons why we continue to return to Bourbon Country.
The service was great, the atmosphere was wonderful, and the food was Superb! Thank you so much.
Awesome spot! Great indoor and outdoor atmosphere and a great menu to compliment the space.

If you are visiting from out of town and looking for guidance in selecting a special Kentucky bourbon, do NOT go here. This restaurant has a spirit shop inside and the staff there is extremely rude, unpleasant, and unwilling to help. I was told this place would be able to recommend a good bourbon only found in Kentucky; however,  the guy is the store was annoyed that I had no knowledge of bourbon and responded to all my questions with nasty remarks. Spend your money elsewhere.
The food was very good, but the service was unorganized and quite slow. We had to ask for drink menus three times before we actually were told they didn't have one.

Very unique setting. Server was good. Ordered a pizza with side salad. Never received salad, pizza was nothing special.  Wife ordered a spicy Chinese dish, they left out the spicy part rendering the dish pretty bland. Dessert was bread pudding with rum sauce. Sauce was tasty but the rest was dry with very little taste.
Cute place with good food. Servers seemed to know thier stuff. A little pricey.
One of my favorite places!  I love the ambiance inside and out!
Great martini's and steaks
Great food.. great service
Great food, great atmosphere! Jazz only on Friday night

Hostess was great, but no waiter existed. Table next to us was seated, brought water, waitress even took a drink order AND brought drinks but refused to even look our way.  After 15 min without water or any sign of a waiter, we left.

Not terrible but not quite stellar. We stopped in for a quick lunch in the theater district on a weekday. It was not too busy and we were enticed by the greeter at the door and the sandwich board advertising $10 lunch combos. We started out with some sweet potato waffle fries which were delicious! Perfectly crisp on the outside, soft inside, dusted with a light coating and finished with flaky salt. We both ordered the lunch combos, mine was the pulled chicken sandwich with a white bean and tomato soup. They sent the soup out separately so they included an heirloom tomato salad that was really good! The soup was a little greasy for my taste which I didn’t expect. I pictured something creamy, but this was almost like a chili. The sandwich was also a surprisingly dry. I pictured a simmered meat in sauce but it was like regular seasoned chicken pieces. The Cuban sandwich was sort of whimpy without much pork. So... there’s room for improvement, but the staff and ambiance were warm and inviting. Hopefully the food catches up!
Friendly woman called to us from hostess stand wishing us a good photo session, so we decided to stop and eat afterwards. Glad we did! Great vegetarian black eyed pea soup and beet/squash entree. Yum
Good
Beautiful atmosphere, amazing patio. Great drinks, get the Manhattan. Wonderful service and Missy is a great hostess and knows a lot about the city.

We happened upon this quaint restaurant.  We opted to sit on the patio and have a few drinks and listen to some jazz,  after visiting with the hostess Missy.  Missy is an amazing hostess and took extra time going over the menu with us.  We will definitely be back.  If you have any questions ask for Missy.

Prices are decent. Desert was delicious.  Ordered the Chicken cordon bleu, it looked different than what I expected, but turned out to be really good. The mashed potatoes and broccoli were good too. The menu is limited and specific but plentiful. While I just had water they had soft drinks and unsweetened tea. Classy restaurant yet inexpensive.  Patio is really relaxing as well if you prefer to eat outside. Service was fast and friendly.  Bathrooms were clean. Would return.

Nice place with Jazz Music. Loved the ambience. Service was excellent. Restaurent have a relaxed feeling  which makes you spend time. Food quality was excellent however the portions were small.  Presentation and taste of the Desert was amazing. Overall, I would certainly recommend this place.

We used the Marketplace for our Rehearsal Dinner for our wedding. At first, I got aggravated as there was a lack of communication on their part. However, despite the delay in responses, everything was figured out in time for the dinner and everything was executed exactly as we planned! The food was delicious! Several of our guests have mentioned this to me several times since the dinner. And the venue was beautiful! We rented the back patio area under the pavilion. I was a little nervous having a dinner outside in June, but it turned out to be wonderful! They were very accommodating and helpful the day of! I would definitely recommend the Marketplace for an event!
Yummy.
Anthony, the bar tender, made our night! He was knowledgeable, and made our stop here one of the best stops on the Kentucky Bourbon     The space is beautiful.
Some of the best cocktails in town! Food excellent too.
Wonderful evening celebrating a wedding rehearsal dinner!
Beautiful venue with excellent customer service. I ordered the filet and it was really good. Great drink selections. Vast bourbon list.
Great Spot in Louisville Great Drinks Food And Atmosphere..... The Pot Roast Was Everything

The food was just okay but the customer service was amazing. I had calamari as an appetizer...it was very pale and unseasoned. I had chicken as my entree, it was a little dry and under seasoned but the kale and yukon mashed potatoes were delicious. I would go back because the customer service was great and I met some amazing people.
Great bar with a nice bourbon selection, good food, and a relaxing atmosphere.

We only had drinks here but that was more than enough. We sat at the bar with Anthony as our bartender. He started off describing this incredible house drink; totally sold me! He was able to recommend a drink for any flavor profile. Every question we asked, he had an answer for. Anthony was so friendly and engaging; he encouraged us to tour the marketplace facility and gave us ideas on where to go in the city. What a friendly and refreshing face; I loved this atmosphere.
This was our first visit. Definitely a nice place to dine. Our meal was wonderful.

Nice ambience, low lighting. Came in with colleagues for dinner. Prices were kind of high especially before currency exchange. I had the garlic herb marinated chicken buttermilk battered and fried. Served with dry mashed potatoes and maple syrup roasted kale!     Not used to having any sweet with my savory. No gravy or sauce to balance our such a dry sweet entree. The other dishes ordered included gnocchi that were doughy and heavy. My friend was very disappointed by this dish. The roasted veg appetizer and salad entree was well received. Only one of us ordered dessert- a unusual take on strawberry shortcake with 3 tiny cookies, strawberries 2 ways including macerated and freeze dried all garnished with a reduced balsamic vinegar syrup. Not what I would have expected for a dessert. Service was attentive and discreet.

I had dinner with some colleagues at Marketplace and it was a bit confusing entering as the patio was opened but there wasn't a door open to enter the build. We thought it was closed. It wasn't until we realized the patio entrance wasn't the right way to enter.  The inside was that of an old theater according to what was told to us. I ordered the Cider Manhattan and it was smooth and delicious. For dinner, I ordered the salmon and it was perfect in every single way. It was cooked perfectly inside and a bit crunchy on top.  I would return as my colleague who ordered the Filet enjoyed every bit of it and thought it was very tender.
Great food and good service. I was surprised that they weren't busier on a Friday night but I don't know Louisville.
Good service just wanted more to choice from especially sides

Before Show Dining  We frequent the Palace and are always looking for new restaurants to try and this was no exception; however, I tried to reserve a table in the past and they go quickly so this time when I ordered my Palace tickets I made our dinner reservations at the same time and we were not disappointed. With all the construction there was a parking advisory but since we had a 5:30 dinner reservation we were able to park very close and since the restaurant is mere steps from the Palace we opted for dessert and coffee following our meal which had us at the theater in plenty of time for the 8:00 performance. When I made the reservation I stated that one of the party was vegetarian and our menu selections reflected that request. The vegetarian had a starter of roasted vegetables and a gnocchi main dish which were excellent! The meat lover of the party enjoyed the poached egg salad on smoked salmon starter followed by lamb shank main course. We shared a pear cobbler with coffee. Everything was exceptional, even the coffee. Our server was attentive and the level of conversation was very comfortable. We are already planning our next visit.

Absolutely fantastic. Good food is one thing (and it is good) but the awesome theme, music, extensive drink menu, professional, knowledgeable, and clean cut staff really make this place a cut above. They make you feel like a sir.
Great food served farm to table
Good cocktails and atmosphere

Waiter hated our table from the start. We ordered salads and appetizers for the table. He brought appetizers,  salads and entrees out at one..we didnt ask for this. Very strange experience. Food was not anything special. Burger was very dry.
Great service, beautiful decor, tasty apps and smooth delicious cocktails. The service is superb from greeting to departure. Definitely a must go
Food was amazing. My waitress was lovely. And i had an amazing time. The menu is reasonably priced and had a lot of choices to pick from. Loved it.
Delicious food , lovely ambience and great friendly service....and did I mentin the food was delicious:)
Very slow service
Put in the back of the restaurant, never stayed on top of our drinks, felt rushed, food was just ok.
Very nice place! Food is incredible and a great atmosphere!
Great bar service.  Very knowledgeable about the regional whiskeys and bourbon.  We come every time we are in town.
The portions are small but very good.  The au-jus is the best I've ever had.
It was just fair.  Better places then this restaurant.
Nice cozy restaurant
Excellent menu!
Food is very good and staff is super friendly
It was decent.
I’ve never had fried artichoke. So yummy. The spinach salad with salmon was amazing. A hot toddy on a cold day was most enjoyed. The decor and atmosphere was lovely.
Nice ambience for date night, but food was not out of this world.
great food, friendly server(Will) and I loved the atmosphere! Wonderful dining experience! I will go back!
Amazing service and great food!!
Wonderful food
Great venue. Food was terrific. Lisa did a fantastic job!
Nice space. Good service. Food is ok.
The staffing there is phenomenal. I attended a private event with the best catered dishes.
A outstanding dinner

Absolute exceptional service. The atmosphere  and ambiance is wonderful and relaxing. Beautiful lighting. Waiters and host, all wonderful. My partner and I came last year also for our anniversary and the chef remembered us. Our food was nothing less than perfect. I can't say enough good things about this place. I wish we had one in TN. We will drive 2 hours every year just for the experience.
Jackson is behind the bar with a great knowledge of cocktail recipes, including pre-prohibition drinks.
Expensive.
We had the place to ourselves!  Great patio and atmosphere.  I wonder why more people are not here!
Service was great, but food quality was subpar, especially for the price.
Menu has changed. Portions are much smaller, but prices are the same. It's not as good as it use to be.
Amazing place amazing food and amazing staff
Beautiful patio, great food & great service.

Went here for an event. They were completely disorganized. Very vauge on what their meal selection entails. Gave us 4 tiny pieces of bread for a table with over 15 people. Aside from that the room looked real nice and the service was nice.
We just finished a great meal. Excellent service. Very accommodating with splitting the meal, gave us a little bit more of the sides. Coming back for dessert after the concert at the Palace Theater.
Great food and service.
the food was bad. The fries were served cold, my duck was raw and almost impossible to chew the vegetables.. very disappointing!!
Service was great. Dessert was amazing.
Service not great.  Had to wait 20 minutes for drink.  Deserts were horrible.  Main dishes good.  Liked atmosphere.
Always amazing food!

Ok, so it was a little pricier than I anticipated, but the food was absolutely amazing.  I liked the atmosphere as well.  We were there for NYE so they had a special (I assume somewhat limited) menu, but my salmon was perfect.
Waited 45 min for service
A little to pricey for restaurant  that serves no bread and has (bad) shoestring french fries for an appetizer . Sea bass and duck were very good
Upscale menu in an intimate setting. We celebrated our 2-year anniversary here with escargot, pork tenderloin, duck and amazing cocktails. Perfect for a special date night!
Wonderful food! Great staff!

I had my son's rehearsal dinner on November 18th.  I worked with Alicia, who was very helpful and was there for the duration.  We had 70 people and a lot of them were from out of town.  The staff was awesome and food was outstanding.  Everyone made our night very special. Thanks to all!!!

I can't believe I've never been here. The host Julian was fabulous! The duck was superb and the hummus appetizer reminded me of Israel. Highly recommended this if you are looking for something WELL worth the money.
Uses local meats and vegetables.
The food was fantastic. The filet was the best I've had in Louisville.
I love this restaurant and the employees are awesome.. service was amazing..great food as well.

Way overpriced.
great atmosphere,decor and food
Nothing special

Absolutely love this place very beautifully set up and so elegant and comfortable with an amazing staff servers are very tentative and on top of things with friendly attitudes as well as the bartenders and the hostess is great she's very sweet friendly and she makes sure no one is ever left waiting when you walk up she's there and ready to assist you with a smile on her face!!!!
Fresh locally sourced food.
For the price, it was a bit disappointing.
Everything  is wonderful for such a small place. Service is always great and a little live music makes the dining even more enjoyable.

Awesome atmosphere, I had the lobster tacos which were good. Wife had steak and potatoes, but the potatoes were smothered in vinager which made us gag. The men's bathroom was disgusting, with a loose urinal wall with pee all over it. I would go back to try other food or drink.

What a great experience! We just had a phenomenal lunch here! My fiancé had a delicious juicy perfectly cooked steak with smashed fingerling potatoes that were perfectly seasoned. I had the lobster tacos, they were awesome too! Strange to say that the most well cooked lobster I've ever eaten came in 10 dollar taco meal! But it's true. These people know what they are doing in the kitchen! For dessert we had a chocolate orange cake with vanilla bean Gelato and candied orange peel garnish. One of the best desserts we have ever eaten. The candied orange peel was such an unexpected treat! Our server was super attentive and treated us like million dollar tipper even though we had lunch specials. Overall....Amazing!!! Thank you Marketplace!
Awesome food and atmosphere. Service was perfect
Of course I love this place!  The outdoor patio is amazing and the staff rocks!

We stopped here for lunch & a drink. It turned into an awesome afternoon of drinks & great food! We learned so much about Louisville from our awesome bartender Bryan! Don't skip this awesome spot while you are in Louisville!

Shopped at the little wine store next to the restaurant. Very friendly staff and dog friendly. Great choices and even better hours. Very few wine stores downtown with a good selection so this place is a gem.
Nice place, clean and friendly people.  Would recommend and good selection

Waited for years to eat here! Had been told by business associates who had been here the I had to try it on my next business trip. Never got the chance. Then when I visited with my husband, we made a point to have dinner at Jack Frys. Better than I could have expected. DELISH! Awesome service.
A bit pricey, but worth it.  I never mind paying a bit more for good food.
Beautiful ambience! Great service! Excellent food!
One of the best hidden secrets in downtown Louisville.  Food is good and great bourbon selection.

Marketplace Restaurant is one of Louisville's hidden gems, about two blocks south of 4th St Live. Definitely worth discovering, the menu is constantly being reinvented and everything I've tasted here has been a work of culinary artistry. The only complaint I can make is having fallen hopelessly in love with a particular menu item (fries tossed in white truffle oil and Parmesan cheese, sprinkled with cilantro and lemon juice and served with a house-made aioli) only for it to disappear from the menu in the following season! C'est la vie. I just have to stay on my toes when it comes to trying new things!
Not good food. Expensive. Small dishes.

Wonderful restaurant in the downtown area. The room is large but still manages a cozy feel. Staff is excellent as is the cocktail selection. Sadly, they recently stopped the live music. When they start live music again, I'll give them 5 stars...
Good food
Food was fresh and well prepared.  Ambiance was nice, Chihuly replicas were a nice touch.
Excellent food and service. Able to accomodate a very large group very well with no notice.

My husband asked the server for his burger cooked medium. She then informed him they only have well done because the beef is pre-cooked for $17.00!! The entree was the fried chicken breast. It was thin and mostly breading which made it hard and crunchy. The pork chop was good but not good enough for $26.00. The server was nice and did not charge us for the chicken but with so many amazing restaurants in louisville they need to step it up fast! Food and cocktails were not up to par for the prices.
Great bourbon selection. They have a lot of hard to find selections.
Greatly reduced their lunch menu, while not bad, just not a lot other than salads to choose from. Service is always slow but food is good.
Amazing food! Upscale atmosphere! Every but of this restaurant has been customized.
Good was good. Thursday night was a bit slow.
Came here just for a cocktail, which was good. Their patio was awesome, a ton of room and could image a very energetic scene later on.
Was here for derby weekend..our party made confirmed reservations...the reservations were conviently disappeared..after some raised voices..finally accommodated us...

Hard to give a review. Were seated outside, watching other tables be seated before we saw a waiter. Had decided on apps, mains, and wine, but still no one - not even a look to flag someone down. Since we didn't even have water, we decided to go get cheap Italian a few doors down. Nice patio, though.

Any place I can use open table to make a reservation is already high in my rankings... So Marketplace gets a leg up for that.  This is a huge place with a very large outdoor area for the warmer months.  The front bar/lounge is inviting with oversized couches and high top tables along with space for live music. I can definitely see myself enjoying Bourbon,  an appetizer, and a live jazz act. The food itself was good,  the menu isn't huge which I prefer... And the price ranges for 16-37 for most entrées.  Had a Chilean sea bass in a honey Chipotle that was pure perfection! (this was the special that evening) My girlfriend had a filet Mignon that, while not mind blowing... Mmm sea bass, was still delicious and prepared as she requested. Service was friendly and relatively fast for a Friday evening. Would highly recommend...conveniently located just beyond Fourth St live,  the Palace, and near the historic Brown hotel.
Great food. Perfect staff. The chicken was marvelous.

I've had dinner here twice.  The first time, I had the burger and was relatively unimpressed.  The second time, I had some short ribs that were absolutely amazing.  Beer list leaves something to be desired, but if liquor is your thing, there's a great selection of cocktails and straight liquors.
Went there for dinner, place was empty and it still took a long time to get our dinner. The waitress had a difficult time keeping our drink order right and way too pricy for what you get.
sea bass was perfect and the mousse was a very sweet and tasty dessert! nice mellow jazz band to add to the ambience this Friday night.
Does not value African American customers, so we will keep our Black dollars and will not patronuze this restaurant
Very good food...even better service. Highly recommend this place.

Amazing and delicious. Go here! Skip Fourth Street Live restaurants and head here for a far superior dining experience.  Marketplace has great food, excellent service and absolutely beautiful decor.  The ambiance and decor are striking and modern.   The outside seating is a real treat in the warmer months. I have lunch and dinner here regularly as it is a very short walk from my office.  I have a lot of experience with Marketplace and I've never been disappointed with any selection on the menu. The menu changes at least seasonally.  This is a locally owned restaurant and I see the owners there nearly every time I visit.

The short ribs were AMAZING!  Huge dinner portion so be warned but worth every bite!  Brussel sprouts were great, too.  Service was excellent especially with me being a single diner. I don't give out a lot of 5 star ratings but the Marketplace Restaurant deserves it!

Everything I had here was amazing but it was a little pricey. The short ribs were prepared in a very unique way, I've never experienced anything like it before. The outside was seared to a dark crust while the insides melted away in your mouth.  I had the short ribs and the bread pudding.

I took my friends out to eat last Friday to marketplace and it was AMAZING! i must admit, after a major let down with the Revue ( Louisville's Rated nicest restaurant) I was hesitant in checking this place out. I'm glad i did! Unbelievably good food, breathtaking entertainment and excellent service! Food was mouthwatering; the singer had an INCREDIBLE voice and our servant made us feel like our table was the most important table in the whole restaurant! Now i am taking my extremely hard-to-please family to marketplace tomorrow. I have no doubt that they will love it!

Wow, what a find!  I casually selected this place while exploring downtown, and I was so happy I did! Delightful atmosphere, good food, knowledgeable wait staff, live jazz - seriously, you can't ask for more. If this was located in DC or Chicago, it would be packed, even on a rainy Wednesday evening.
Stopped in after breast walk 10/11/14. First visit . Food , drinks, atmosphere and service were excellent ! Jewell of a place !

Walked here from the nearby Brown Hotel for dinner at 7:30pm on a Tuesday night. I was the only person on the place (that should have been a clue).  While The BBQ pulled pork risotto fritter appetizer had excellent taste, the NY strip steak was full of fat and gristle. ISteaks at Outback are better quality. The purple potato purée and greens underneath the steak were bland. I was so disappointed I skipped dessert. Maybe it was just a bad night, but I would advise ordering a steak here. There are a lot of good restaurants in town, I doubt I will come back.
That was not a prime steak I just paid $28 for!

I've been here for an opera after party and lunch.  Both times were great experiences.  Lots of great glass fixtures.  The place is very attractive inside--not something you'd expect in Louisville.  I think they've changed up the menu recently since it was different than the last time I was there.  Lunch has a variety of salads, sandwiches, and a few entrees, presented in an appealing way.  Details like thick cut bacon and homemade thick chips.  The drinks have fun details like sprigs of rosemary.  Sometimes there's live music, such as a piano player.  The only downside is that it's never crowded, so there isn't a vibrant scene there.  (Yet...)  I hope Louisville catches on.
